淋巴结清扫数目对7 5 岁及以上老年食管癌患者 预后影响的分析
李强明，张国庆，刘天阳，赵 松 ，李向楠 郑州大学第一附属医院胸外科，郑 州 450052

摘 要 ：目 的 探 讨 淋 巴 结 清 扫 的 数 目 对 7 5 岁及以上老年食管癌患者预后的影响。方 法 回 顾 性 分 析 1998年 _ 2015年 美 国 The Surveillance, Epidemiology, and E n d Results (S E E R )数据库中行食管癌根治术并淋巴结清扫的 老年患者临床病理资料。根据淋巴结清扫的数目将患者分为A 组 （清 扫 1 - 1 4 枚 淋 巴 结 ）和 B 组 （清 扫 在 1 5 枚 淋巴结），比较两组患者围手术期死亡率（P 0 M )和 远 期 预 后 。结 果 共 有 6 7 7 例 患 者 纳 人 本 研 究 ，A 组 4 2 9 例 (63. 4 % ) ,B 组 2 4 8 例 （36. 6 % ) 。A 组 和 B 组 患 者 术 后 3 0 天围手术期死亡率（30 - P 0 M )分 别 为 5. 8 % 和 4. 4 % (P =0. 437) ;60 - P 0 M 分别为 9. 1 % 和 7. 3 % ( P =0. 408) ;90 - P 0 M 分别为 11. 9 % 和为 9. 3 % ( P =0. 294);差异 无统计学意义。A 组 和 B 组中位生存时间分别为2 5 个 月 和 3 7 个 月 ；1 年生存率分别为65. 9 % 和 "73. 3 % ;3年生 存 率 分 别 为 42. 1 % 和 50. 3 % ;5年 生 存 率 分 别 为 32. 1 % 和 4〇.7% ;差异有统计学意义（P = 0. 0 3 6 ) 。多 因 素 C 〇x 分析显示，广泛的淋巴结清扫（X 2 = 丨3. 226，H R =0. 697,95_% C I 为 0. 573 ~ 0. 847，P <0. 001)是影响患者长期预 后的独立危险因素。结 论 7 5 岁 及 以 上 老 年食 管 癌 患 者 可 以 从 广 泛 的 淋 巴 结 清 扫 中 获 益 ，而不会增加患者围 手术期死亡风险。 关键词:食管癌;老年患者;淋巴结清扫;预后分析;S E E R 数据库 中图分类号:R 735.1 文献标识码：B 文 章 编 号 ：1672-3422(2020)1(M )021"07

A prognostic analysis on extensive of lymph node resection for the elderly patients with esophageal cancer

LI Qiang - ming, ZHANG Guo - qing, LIU Tian - yang, ZHAO Song, LI Xiang - nan Department of Thoracic Surgery, the First Affiliated Hospital of Zhengzhou University, Zhengzhou 4 5 0 0 5 2 ,China

Abstract ：Objective To explore the prognostic value of the number of lymph node resection for the elderly patients

(aged ^ 7 5 years) with esophageal cancer. Methods The SEER database was examined for surgically resected esopha­

geal carcinoma and included the elderly patients ( aged ^ 7 5 years) from 1998 to 2015. We divided the patients into two

groups by the number of lymph node dissection：group A ( patients with 1 - 1 4 examined lymph nodes) and group B

(patients with^ 1 5 examined lymph nodes) , respectively. Postoperative mortality ( POM) and overall survival ( O S) of

the two groups were quantified. Results A total of 677 the elderly patients with thoracic esophageal cancer underwent

esophagectomy with ^ 1 lymph node dissection enrolled in the analysis, including 429 patients(63. 4% ) in group A and

248 patients(36. 6 % ) in group B, respectively. The 30 - day POM rates were 5. 8% and 4. 4% ( P = 0. 437) , the 60 -

day POM rates were 9. 1% and 7. 3% ( 尸=0. 4 0 8 ) , and the 90 - day POM rates were 11 • 9% and 9. 3% ( 户= 0. 294)

between patients with group A and group B , respectively. However, the differences in POM between the two groups were

statistically nonsignificant. The median survival time were 25and 37 months, the 1 - year OS rates were 65. 9% and

73. 3% , the 3 - year OS rates were 42. 1% and 50. 3% , and the 5 - year OS rates were 32. 1% and 40. 7% between

patients with group A and group B , respectively. There was significant difference in terms of long - term survival ( P =

0. 036) • According to our multivariable Cox proportional hazards model analysis, extensive lymph node dissection ( \ 2 =

13. 2 2 6 ， HR = 0. 6 9 7 ,95% Cl :0• 573 〜0. 847 <0• 001 }was the independent risk factor for the long - term survival in

___________________________________

the elderly patients ( aged ^ 75 years ) after esophagectomy.

